The greedy eyes of foreign MEPs 'photograph' the unprecedented pause from the political agon during the visit to the monastery after the Mass at the Sacred Spec of Subiaco>. A caresss to the statue of San Benedetto>, a look at the breathtaking panorama from the rocky hill in the upper Aniene Valley, the inevitable selfies. Then the journey back to the country between the hairpin bends, illuminated by the torch at the edge of the road and the off-plan of a mother who chases through the woods the young boy scout (in night trip) to bring him the jacket.
