The sense of the initiative is summed up by the words of the Conservatives' co-president in the European Parliament, Nicola Procaccini>. "In these years we have tried to place the Ventotene Manifesto in the heart of the construction of Europe as if it were a kind of sacred text. This - says to AGI the Euro MP of Brothers of Italy - is a historical forcing because it was a respectable text but of part that has nothing to do with Europe that was then planned that it was a confederal and not federalist Europe. This is the right opportunity to say that Europe is the daughter of Saint Benedict, of the patron of Europe and is certainly not the daughter of Spinelli or of others, respectable characters of our history also heroic, courageous but from an ideal point of view the core of European identity is here in Subiaco is not in Ventotene".
