AGI -&nbsp;&nbsp;"I come here with the hope that today's debate finds us all with the awareness of the serious time" we are going through, there is the need to reason together, even in the divisions between political forces, "with the sense of responsibility". "We find ourselves on the eve of a European Council which falls at an extremely complex moment for global events, and at the same time decisive for the fate of Italy, of Western Europe," said the Prime Minister. One must "try to think together what are the best choices for our nation", he said.&nbsp;
<h2> A trade war would not benefit anyone
The subject of duties is not on the agenda of the European Council but "it is a point to be taken into consideration", the Trump administration " decided to reactivate the duties", the picture is complex and constantly evolving". This was said by the President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni, during the communications in the Chamber to the Senate in view of the European Council of 20 and 21 March. "It is not wise to fall into the vicious circle of reprisals," he added. "I'm not sure it's a good deal to answer duties with other duties," he said.
<h2>Do not fall into the temptation of reprisals
On the subject of duties, "I believe it is not wise to fall into the temptation of reprisals that become a vicious circle in which everyone loses". If it is true that the duties imposed on non-EU goods can theoretically favour internal production, in a context strongly interconnected as that of European and American economies, the framework is complicated." The President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni, said this in the Senate House in his communications to the European Council on Thursday and Friday. "The duties - Meloni has added - can easily be translated into induced inflation, with the consequent reduction of the purchasing power of the families and the subsequent increase of the rates from the ECB to counter the inflationary phenomenon, as we have already seen. Result: inflation and monetary tightening of economic growth. I am not sure, in short, that it is necessarily a good deal to respond to duties with other duties. For this reason, I believe that the energies of Italy must be spent in search of solutions of common sense between the United States and Europe, dictated more by logic than by instinct, in an optical of mutual respect and economic convenience".
<h2>ReArm EU? It is not rearmament, it is defense</h2>
On the 'ReArm Ue' "I asked to change name, because the name is misleading for citizens. We are called to strengthen defensive skills, but "does not mean to buy weapons" but "if anything to produce them" by strengthening "our productive fabric. Strengthening the capabilities of Defense>" does not mean "only arsenals. Safety" is a "very vast" section.<br> Premier Giorgia Meloni said that, speaking to the Senate. "Without defence there is no security, no security there is no freedom," said the President of the Council, "change the name to the ReArm Ue is not a semantic question, but of substance and merit. With the resources to provisions you can finance subjects" which should interest everyone, said Meloni. "Italy does not intend to remove only one euro from the resources of the Cohesion," he said.
<h2>Mai support for Kiev
"But in question" support in Kiev, "this commitment we sell it, Italy has a clear position, respects its international commitments. It's a nation whose opinion counts." So Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni in the Senate Hall in communications for the EU Council.&nbsp;
<h2>No to green deal, but with a different name
"We will continue to insist on an effective industrial policy, which can combine environmental objectives with competitiveness, renouncing the ideological excesses we have unfortunately seen and denounced in the past. The Clean Industrial Deal presented by the Commission goes in this direction, but it is clear that we intend to prevent it from becoming a new Green Deal with a different name. To do so we ask for concrete actions. The first of these cannot but concern the car sector, a strategic industrial sector for Europe that cannot be abandoned to its own destiny". The President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni, said this in the Senate House in his communications to the European Council on Thursday and Friday.
<h2> The cards in order to cross the storm</h2>
"With a clear vision Italy has all the cards in rules to cross this storm too," "we will put all the courage it needs." Thus Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni, concluding his communications to the Senate in view of the Ue.&nbsp Council;
